definition: to move/to shift/to change/to alter/to remove
to get rid of/to remove/to exclude/to eliminate/to wipe out/to divide/except/not including

sentences.english: So, suppose I want to remove something.

sentences.english: Rayon of permanent and can be removed.

sentences.english: Surgical removal of a breast cyst is necessary only in a few unusual circumstances.
sentences.chinese: 只有在不得已的情况下才有必要做手术移除乳腺囊肿。

sentences.english: Please consider to remove the Latin fonts prior to the CJK fonts.

sentences.english: Dislodgement of clot can lead to embolic phenomena, including stroke.

sentences.english: It cannot be dropped and you cannot add or remove users from it.
sentences.chinese: 您无法加以卸除，也无法从其加入或移除使用者。

sentences.english: That means a single added or removed space will invalidate the signature.
sentences.chinese: 这意味着添加或者移除一个空格将会使签名无效。

sentences.english: This optimization removes invariant subexpressions from the body of a loop.
sentences.chinese: 此优化将不变量子表达式从循环体中移除。

sentences.english: I must delete the message if I wish to permanently remove it from processing.
sentences.chinese: 如果我希望永久地从处理中移除消息，我必须删除它。

sentences.english: Attunements to enter Heroic instances will be removed.

sentences.english: This was a part of that ship easily separated from the vessel and turned into the rot.

sentences.english: We have also removed both the short- and long-term ratings from CreditWatch negative.
sentences.chinese: 我们也将短期与长期评级从信用观察负面中移除。

sentences.english: The gridline and its corresponding row or column is removed.
sentences.chinese: 格线和其对应资料列或资料行随即遭移除。

sentences.english: The additional 2 seconds cooldown added on abilities while Shadow Dance is active has been removed.
